Name: build_existing_model.emissions_electricity_folders
Description: Relative paths of electricity emissions factor schedule files with hourly values. Paths are relative to the resources folder. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list. File names must contain GEA region names.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_electricity_units
Description: Electricity emissions factors units. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list. Only lb/MWh and kg/MWh are allowed.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_electricity_values_or_filepaths
Description: Electricity emissions factors values, specified as either an annual factor or an absolute/relative path to a file with hourly factors. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_fossil_fuel_units
Description: Fossil fuel emissions factors units. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list. Only lb/MBtu and kg/MBtu are allowed.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_fuel_oil_values
Description: Fuel oil emissions factors values, specified as an annual factor. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_natural_gas_values
Description: Natural gas emissions factors values, specified as an annual factor. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_propane_values
Description: Propane emissions factors values, specified as an annual factor. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_scenario_names
Description: Names of emissions scenarios. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_types
Description: Types of emissions (e.g., CO2e, NOx, etc.). If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.emissions_wood_values
Description: Wood emissions factors values, specified as an annual factor. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.hvac_has_zonal_electric_heating

Name: build_existing_model.insulation_rim_joist
Description: TODO

Name: build_existing_model.sample_weight
Description: Number of buildings this simulation represents.

Name: build_existing_model.simulation_control_run_period_begin_day_of_month
Description: This numeric field should contain the starting day of the starting month (must be valid for month) for the annual run period desired.

Name: build_existing_model.simulation_control_run_period_begin_month
Description: This numeric field should contain the starting month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the annual run period desired.

Name: build_existing_model.simulation_control_run_period_calendar_year
Description: This numeric field should contain the calendar year that determines the start day of week. If you are running simulations using AMY weather files, the value entered for calendar year will not be used; it will be overridden by the actual year found in the AMY weather file.

Name: build_existing_model.simulation_control_run_period_end_day_of_month
Description: This numeric field should contain the ending day of the ending month (must be valid for month) for the annual run period desired.

Name: build_existing_model.simulation_control_run_period_end_month
Description: This numeric field should contain the end month number (1 = January, 2 = February, etc.) for the annual run period desired.

Name: build_existing_model.simulation_control_timestep
Description: Value must be a divisor of 60.

Name: build_existing_model.units_represented
Description: The number of dwelling units this simulation represents. Should always be one.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_electricity_fixed_charges
Description: Electricity utility bill monthly fixed charges. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_electricity_marginal_rates
Description: Electricity utility bill marginal rates. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_fuel_oil_fixed_charges
Description: Fuel oil utility bill monthly fixed charges. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_fuel_oil_marginal_rates
Description: Fuel oil utility bill marginal rates. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_natural_gas_fixed_charges
Description: Natural gas utility bill monthly fixed charges. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_natural_gas_marginal_rates
Description: Natural gas utility bill marginal rates. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_propane_fixed_charges
Description: Propane utility bill monthly fixed charges. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_propane_marginal_rates
Description: Propane utility bill marginal rates. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_pv_compensation_types
Description: Utility bill PV compensation types. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_pv_feed_in_tariff_rates
Description: Utility bill PV annual full/gross feed-in tariff rates. Only applies if the PV compensation type is 'FeedInTariff'. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_pv_monthly_grid_connection_fee_units
Description: Utility bill PV monthly grid connection fee units. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_pv_monthly_grid_connection_fees
Description: Utility bill PV monthly grid connection fees. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_pv_net_metering_annual_excess_sellback_rate_types
Description: Utility bill PV net metering annual excess sellback rate types. Only applies if the PV compensation type is 'NetMetering'. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_pv_net_metering_annual_excess_sellback_rates
Description: Utility bill PV net metering annual excess sellback rates. Only applies if the PV compensation type is 'NetMetering' and the PV annual excess sellback rate type is 'User-Specified'. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_scenario_names
Description: Names of utility bill scenarios. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_wood_fixed_charges
Description: Wood utility bill monthly fixed charges. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.utility_bill_wood_marginal_rates
Description: Wood utility bill marginal rates. If multiple scenarios, use a comma-separated list.

Name: build_existing_model.weather_file_city
Description: City from the EPW weather file.

Name: build_existing_model.weather_file_latitude
Description: Latitude from the EPW weather file.

Name: build_existing_model.weather_file_longitude
Description: Longitude from the EPW weather file.
